{"title_page": "Smederevska Palanka", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name              = Smederevska Palanka\n| native_name       = \u0421\u043c\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0430\u043b\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430\n| native_name_lang  = sr\n| other_name        = \n| settlement_type   = [[List of cities in Serbia|Town]] and [[Municipalities and cities of Serbia|municipality]]\n| official_name     = \n| nickname          = \n| motto             = \n| image_shield      = Veliki grb Smederevske Palanke.png\n| image_flag        = \n| image_skyline     = Smederevska Palanka - pogled.jpg\n| image_caption     = \n| image_map         = Municipalities of Serbia Smederevska Palanka.png\n| map_caption       = Location of the municipality of Smederevska Palanka within Serbia\n| mapsize           = \n| coordinates       = {{coord|44|21.98|N|20|57.39|E|region:RS|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type  = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name  = {{flag|Serbia}}\n| subdivision_type1 = [[Subdivisions of Serbia|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Southern and Eastern Serbia]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[Districts of Serbia|District]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Podunavlje District|Podunavlje]]\n| parts_type        = Settlements\n| parts_style       = para\n| p1                = 18\n| leader_title      = Mayor\n| leader_name       = Petar Mili\u0107\n| leader_party      = [[Serbian Progressive Party|SNS]]\n| area_blank1_title = Town\n| area_blank1_km2   = 21.72\n| area_blank2_title = Municipality\n| area_blank2_km2   = 422\n| area_footnotes    = <ref>{{Serbian municipalities 2006}}</ref><ref name=\"areasp\">{{cite web |title=\u041d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u0459\u0430 \u043e\u043f\u0448\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0435 \u0421\u043c\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0430\u043b\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430 |url=http://webrzs.stat.gov.rs/axd/Registar/SlikeRegioni/Mapiranemape/CentralnaSrbija/ReSmederevskaPalanka.pdf |website=stat.gov.rs |accessdate=21 March 2019 |language=Serbian}}</ref>\n| elevation_m       = 125\n| population_footnotes = <ref>{{Serbian census 2011}}</ref>\n| population_as_of  = 2011 census\n| population_blank1_title = Town\n| population_blank1 = 23601\n| population_density_blank1_km2 = auto\n| population_blank2_title = Municipality\n| population_blank2 = 50284\n| population_density_blank2_km2 = auto\n| timezone          = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset        = +1\n| timezone_DST      = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST    = +2\n| postal_code_type  = [[Postal codes in Serbia|Postal code]]\n| postal_code       = 11420\n| area_code_type    = [[Telephone numbers in Serbia|Area code]]\n| area_code         = +381(0)26\n| blank_name        = [[Vehicle registration plates of Serbia|Car plates]]\n| blank_info        = SP\n| website           = {{url|www.smederevskapalanka.rs}}\n}}\n'''Smederevska Palanka''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|\u0421\u043c\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0430\u043b\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430}}, {{IPA-sh|sm\u025b\u0302d\u025br\u025b\u028bska p\u01cela\u02d0\u014bka|pron}}) is a town and municipality located in the [[Podunavlje District]] and the geographical region of [[\u0160umadija]]. According to the 2011 census, the town has 23,601, while the municipality has 50,284 inhabitants.\n\n==History==\nIn the vicinity of the town there are two archaeological sites: [[Medvednjak]], near [[Gr\u010dac]], and Staro Selo, near [[Selevac]]. They belong to the end of [[Neolithic]] and early [[Eneolithic]], or the period 4500-3500 BC, during the developed and ending phase of the [[Vin\u010da culture]] when the first evidence of metallurgy appeared. The culture then disappears as the population presumably migrated. Both settlements were large, spreading on {{convert|40|to|60|ha|abbr=on}}. Findings from the later [[Hallstatt culture]] were also discovered. The most important artifacts, kept in the People's Museum in Smederevska Palanka, are the anthropomorphic figurines of high artistic and artisan value. One of the most valuable and considered unique is the one called \"Woman in labor\", due to its contracted position. In total, there are over 1,000 figurines, some complete, some damaged, but it is estimated that at least 3,000 of them are in personal collections.<ref>{{Citation | author = Olivera Milo\u0161evi\u0107 | title = Figurine iz palana\u010dkih nalazi\u0161ta putuju u Evropu | trans-title = Figurines from the Palanka sites travel to Europe | newspaper = [[Politika]] | page = 14 | language = Serbian | date = 19 November 2017 }}</ref>\n\nThere are also numerous finds from both [[Ancient Rome|Roman]] and [[Medieval]] periods. The most unusual of these finds is the [[cameo (carving)|cameo]] in two-layered onyx of Emperor [[Constantine I]] in full battle gear on a horse which was discovered near Kusadak, a village in the Smederevka Palanka municipality.\n\nThe town was first mentioned in 1021, in a written document currently preserved in St. Catherine's monastery in [[Egypt]].{{citation_needed|date=March 2019}}\n\n==Climate==\nSmederevska Palanka has a [[humid subtropical climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification]]: ''Cfa''), bordering an [[oceanic climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification]]: ''Cfb''). Smederevska Palanka holds the Serbian national record for the highest temperature ever recorded with {{convert|44.9|\u00b0C|1|abbr=on}}, on 24 July 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.meteosrbija.rs/meteomagazin1/21-najtoplija-mesta-na-svetu.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-06-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120510094725/http://www.meteosrbija.rs/meteomagazin1/21-najtoplija-mesta-na-svetu.html |archivedate=2012-05-10 }}</ref>\n{{Weather box\n|width = auto\n|location = Smederevska Palanka (1981\u20132010, extremes 1961\u20132010)\n|single line = Yes\n|metric first = Yes\n|Jan record high C = 20.6\n|Feb record high C = 24.4\n|Mar rec