ac]] (3381)\n* [[Stoja\u010dak]] (364)\n* [[Vla\u0161ki Do (Smederevska Palanka)|Vla\u0161ki Do]] (971)\n* [[Vodice (Smederevska Palanka)|Vodice]] (881)\n{{col div end}}\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Historical populations\n| type = \n| percentages = pagr\n|1948|50306 |1953|53039 |1961|55488 |1971|58112 |1981|60945 |1991|59822 |2002|56011 |2011|50284\n| source = <ref>{{cite web|title=2011 Census of Population, Households and Dwellings in the Republic of Serbia|url=http://pod2.stat.gov.rs/ObjavljenePublikacije/Popis2011/Knjiga20.pdf|website=stat.gov.rs|publisher=Statistical Office of the Republic of Serbia|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref>\n}}\nAs of 2011 census, the municipality has 50,284 inhabitants.\n\n===Ethnic groups===\nThe ethnic composition of the municipality:<ref>{{cite web|title=\u041f\u043e\u043f\u0438\u0441 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0448\u0442\u0432\u0430, \u0434\u043e\u043c\u0430\u045b\u0438\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u0438 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430 2011. \u0443 \u0420\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0438 \u0421\u0440\u0431\u0438\u0458\u0438|url=http://pod2.stat.gov.rs/ObjavljenePublikacije/Popis2011/Nacionalna%20pripadnost-Ethnicity.pdf|website=stat.gov.rs|publisher=Republi\u010dki zavod za statistiku|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref>\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Ethnic group\n! Population\n|-\n|style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\"|[[Serbs]]||align=\"right\"|47,972\n|-\n|style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\"|[[Romani people in Serbia|Roma]]||align=\"right\"|563\n|-\n|style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\"|[[Macedonians in Serbia|Macedonians]]||align=\"right\"|115\n|-\n|style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\"|[[Montenegrins of Serbia|Montenegrins]]||align=\"right\"|81\n|-\n|style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\"|[[Croats of Serbia|Croats]]||align=\"right\"|63\n|-\n|style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\"|[[Yugoslavs in Serbia|Yugoslavs]]||align=\"right\"|43\n|-\n|style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\"|[[Hungarians in Serbia|Hungarians]]||align=\"right\"|22\n|-\n|style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\"|Others||align=\"right\"|1,425\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n|style=\"background:#F0F0F0;\"|'''Total'''||align=\"right\"|50,284\n|}\n\n==Society and culture==\n[[File:Crkva brvnara Svetog Ilije.jpg|thumb|right|230px|St. Elijah wooden church]]\n\n===Culture===\nThere are currently three [[Serbian Orthodox]] churches in Smederevska Palanka.\n\nThe oldest, the church of [[St. Elijah]] was built in 1827 and is one of the oldest wooden churches in Serbia. The town's Cathedral Church was built in 1902. The town's newest church, [[St. Petka (Smederevska Palanka)|St. Petka]], was built in 1997. The town's fourth Serbian orthodox church is under construction. [[Koporin Monastery]], built in 1402 by Serbian prince [[Stefan Lazarevi\u0107]], lies just outside the town in [[Velika Plana]].\n\n===Education===\nSmederevska Palanka has four elementary schools: Vuk Karad\u017ei\u0107, Heroj Radmila \u0160i\u0161kovi\u0107, Heroj Ivan Muker and Olga Milo\u0161evi\u0107. The town has three high schools: Palanka Gymnasium, Go\u0161a Technical School, and \"\u017dikica Damjanovi\u0107\" Chemical and Medical School.\n\nSmederevska Palanka has two local operating radio-television stations; \"Jasenica\" and \"Devi\u0107\".\n\n===Events===\nAnnually every June, the town hosts the [[Best Fest Palanka]], a rock festival featuring famous Serbian bands including [[Mom\u010dilo Bajagi\u0107|Bajaga]], [[Riblja \u010dorba]], [[Mar\u010delo]], Six pack band, Sunshine rap group and others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.izlazak.com/index.php/muzika/1634-best-fest-palanka-rok-festival-opsirnije|title=BEST FEST PALANKA / ROK FESTIVAL|first=|last=Katarina|website=Izlazak.com|accessdate=28 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nSmederevska Palanka has one of Serbia's oldest annual traditional fairs, the [[Krstovdanski Va\u0161ar]] which has been held since 1834 when it was introduced by Prince [[Milo\u0161 Obrenovi\u0107]]. During the fair, the town is visited by 100,000 to 150,000 tourists from surrounding towns and cities.\n\nSmederevska Palanka hosts the \"Motorijada\", where thousands of bikers from Serbia and the former Yugoslavia assemble for the event and live concerts in Smederevska Palanka's Kiseljak. The 2011 event featured a famous Yugoslav band, [[Divlje Jagode]].\n\n===Tourism===\nBeside archaeological findings and medieval monasteries, famous touristic spots in Smederevska Palanka include lake [[Kudre\u010d]], the [[Kiseljak spa|Kiseljak]] spa complex and [[Mikulja forest|Mikulja]] forest.\n\nSmederevska Palanka has a natural mineral water spring which is said to have been used since Roman times, and has been used by the surrounding peoples since at least 1719.{{citation_needed|date=March 2019}} On 22 April 1907, the water from the mineral springs was awarded the golden medal for quality at the London 'Balkan Fair'.\n\nAccording to some researchers, the town's mineral water is the 3rd best in Europe, primarily due to the natural [[selenium]] it contains.{{citation_needed|date=March 2019}}\n\n==Economy==\n[[File:\u017delezni\u010dka stanica u Smederevskoj Palanci.jpg|thumb|right|230px|Smederevska Palanka railway station, built in 1884.]]\nSmederevska Palanka is an important industrial town, primarily due to the influence of manufacturing company [[Go\u0161a FOM]] which was among the biggest companies in the former Yugoslavia. The company produces trams, train wagons as well as prefabricated steel constructions.\n\nOther industries and businesses based in Smederevska Palanka include \"Kara\u0111or\u0111e\", a company which produces mineral water and juice, \"[[Vo\u0107ar Palanka]]\" a food manufacturer and fruit supplier as well as \"[[Opeka Palanka]]\", a bricks and building material manufacturer.\n\nAdditionally, Smederevska Palanka operates an Institute of Agriculture which researches seeds and vegetables.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.institut-palanka.co.rs/index.php?cls=_loadPage&m=showSorts&sid=1|title=Po\u010detna - Institut za povrtarstvo|website=Institut-palanka.co.rs|accessdate=28 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe following table gives a preview of total number of registered people employed in legal entities per their core activity (as of 2018):<ref name=\"stats18\">{{cite web|title=MUNICIPALITIES AND REGIONS OF THE REPUBLIC OF SERBIA, 2019.|url=https://publikacije.stat.gov.rs/G2019/PdfE/G201913046.pdf|website=stat.gov.rs|publisher=[[Statistical Office of the Republic of Serbia]]|date=25 December 2019|accessdate=28 December 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n! Activity\n! Total\n|-\n|Agriculture, forestry and fishing||align=\"right\"|163\n|-\n|Mining and quarrying||align=\"right\"|-\n|-\n|Manufacturing||align=\"right\"|2,265\n|-\n|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply||align=\"right\"|52\n|-\n|Water supply; sewerage, waste management and remediation activities||align=\"right\"|175\n|-\n|Construction||align=\"right\"|481\n|-\n|Wholesale and retail trade, repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles||align=\"right\"|1,385\n|-\n|Transportation and storage||align=\"right\"|327\n|-\n|Accommodation and food services||align=\"right\"|196\n|-\n|Information and communication||align=\"right\"|78\n|-\n|Financial and insurance activities||align=\"right\"|94\n|-\n|Real estate activities||align=\"right\"|32\n|-\n|Professional, scientific and technical activities||align=\"right\"|324\n|-\n|Administrative and support service activities||align=\"right\"|141\n|-\n|Public administration and defense; compulsory social security||align=\"right\"|445\n|-\n|Education||align=\"right\"|682\n|-\n|Human health and social work activities||align=\"right\"|1,139\n|-\n|Arts, entertainment and recreation||align=\"right\"|137\n|-\n|Other service activities||align=\"right\"|177\n|-\n|Individual agricultural workers||align=\"right\"|989\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n|'''Total'''||align=\"right\"|'''9,282'''\n|}\n\n==Transportation==\n[[File:043 Smederevska Palanka, Serbia.jpg|thumb|right|230px|Aerial view]]\nSmederevska Palanka lies on [[A1 motorway (Serbia)|A1 motorway]], which is part of [[Pan-European Corridor X]]. It is also at the route of the Belgrade-Ni\u0161 railway. The town's railway station was built in 1884.{{citation_needed|date=March 2019}}\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Smederevska_Palanka_Sud.jpg|\nFile:SPalanka_Kralja_Petra_I.jpg|\nFile:SP_Ulica_Prvog_srpskog_ustanka.jpg|\nFile:Stara \u010dar\u0161ija SP.jpg|\nFile:SPalanka, Crkva Svetog Preobra\u017eenja.jpg|\nFile:Crkva Svete Petke, Smederevska Palanka.jpg|\nFile:Kolonija, Smederevska Palanka.jpg|\nFile:Zgrade u Kralja Petra I.jpg|\nFile:Soliter Rudnik.jpg|\nFile:Tr\u017eni centar Oblik.jpg|\nFile:Hotel jezero kudre\u010d.jpg|\nFile:Tr\u017eni centar Nama.jpg|\n</gallery>\n\n==Notable people==\nSome of the notable people of Smederevska Palanka are:\n* [[Stanoje Glava\u0161]], [[First Serbian Uprising]] hero\n* [[Miloje Popovi\u0107 \u0110ak]]\n* [[Vujica Vuli\u0107evi\u0107]]\n* [[Josip Broz Tito]], statesman, lived in Smederevska Palanka and was employed as a metalworker here\n* [[Vladimir Raki\u0107evi\u0107]], researcher\n* [[\u017divko Pavlovi\u0107]], general\n* [[Perica Ognjenovi\u0107]], a football player\n* [[Zdenko Muf]], a football player\n* [[Radmila Milentijevi\u0107]], former minister\n* [[Veljko Tatalovi\u0107]], zanatlija\n* [[Pera Todorovi\u0107]], journalist\n* [[Aran\u0111el Marki\u0107evi\u0107]] Minister of Justice 1994-1998\n* [[Mina Milutinovi\u0107]], Miss World Next Top Model 2012\n* [[Ivan Na\u010dkovi\u0107]], Russian born, lives in Smederevska Palanka, musician\n\n==International cooperation==\nSmederevska Palanka is twinned with [[\u0160kofja Loka]] in [[Slovenia]]. Before the [[Yugoslav wars]], the two towns had a joint art colony [[Groharjeva kolonija]].\n\nAfter the first World War, one street in the center of Smederevska Palanka was named Francuska, or [https://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&ie=UTF8&hq=&ll=44.364556,20.958368 French street] while a street in the French city of [[Grenoble]] was named after [https://maps.google.com/maps?client=firefox-a&hl=en&ie=UTF8&hq=&hnear=Rue+de+Palanka,+38000+Grenoble,+Is%C3%A8re,+Rh%C3%B4ne-Alpes,+France&ll=45.191048,5.723968&spn=0.00093,0.002411&z=19 Palanka] as a way of celebrating the friendship between Serbia and France.\n\n==Twin towns==\n{{See also|List of twin towns and sister cities in Serbia}}\n\nSmederevska Palanka is [[Twin towns and sister cities|twinned]] with:\n* {{flagicon|BIH}} [[Br\u010dko]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n* {{flagicon|Slovenia}} [[\u0160kofja Loka]], [[Slovenia]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[Municipalities of Serbia]]\n* [[Cities and towns in Serbia]]\n* [[List of populated places in Serbia|Populated places of Serbia]]\n* [[Smederevska Palanka Airport]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|Smederevska Palanka}}\n* {{official website|www.smederevskapalanka.rs}}\n\n{{Municipalities and cities of Southern and Eastern Serbia|state=expanded}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Podunavlje District]]\n[[Category:Municipalities and cities of Southern and Eastern Serbia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name              = Smederevska Palanka\n| native_name       = \u0421\u043c\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0430\u043b\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430\n| native_name_lang  = sr\n| other_name        = \n| settlement_type   = [[List of cities in Serbia|Town]] and [[Municipalities and cities of Serbia|municipality]]\n| official_name     = \n| nickname          = \n| motto             = \n| image_shield      = Veliki grb Smederevske Palanke.png\n| image_flag        = \n| image_skyline     = Smederevska Palanka - pogled.jpg\n| image_caption     = \n| image_map         = Municipalities of Serbia Smederevska Palanka.png\n| map_caption       = Location of the municipality of Smederevska Palanka within Serbia\n| mapsize           = \n| coordinates       = {{coord|44|21.98|N